The paper focuses on the economics and social aspects of daily deal sites, which involves analyzing user behavior and social network effects. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of social computing (cs.SI, cs.SOC), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), machine learning (cs.MA), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
